<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="592" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Powell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-11"><hi rend="italic">May 11,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Powell reports that the situation at Port au Prince is extremely
                            interesting, it being reported that the President will probably leave on
                            May 12, in which event bloodshed is feared; that the south demands the
                            Presidency; that Firmin and Leconte are candidates from the north.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>